==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pollex
<hw>Pol"lex</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Pollices</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[the thumb.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The first, or preaxial, digit of the fore limb,
corresponding to the hallux in the hind limb; the thumb. In birds, the
pollex is the joint which bears the bastard wing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pollicate</ent>⟦br⟧
